  "id": "51b4de20ad40f390",
  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/snowflake/f17e8a6d-8af5-40c9-b8d4-4a26f22f2503/application",
    "company": "Snowflake",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "51b4de20ad40f390",
    "department": "Marketing",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nSnowflake is looking for a Field Marketing Coordinator, based in our Tel Aviv office. As a Field Marketing Coordinator, you are responsible for supporting the South Marketing team in planning and executing event campaigns, demand generation programs, and account-based marketing activities. We’re looking for a passionate self-starter who wants to gain valuable hands-on experience and help build awareness in the region, drive and nurture leads, and accelerate opportunities to close.\n\n\nThe ideal candidate is a self-motivated team player who is extremely organized and eager to learn. The candidate should be able to handle and adapt to a fast pace environment that is frequently changing. The candidate will have to undertake numerous projects simultaneously which they should be able to balance.\n\nJob Description:\n\n - Support the regional Field Marketing Managers with executing Marketing activities for the region including 3rd party industry conferences, Snowflake-driven physical event series, regional hospitality, online activities and direct mailings\n\n - Maintain the Snowflake online calendar of events\n\n - Drive logistics and execution of all planned events; work with outside vendors, oversee fulfilment/inventory levels\n\n - Coordinating with third party providers such as external agencies, event organizers\n\n - Maintain direct alignment with sales team in terms of all pre and post event communication, marketing-driven campaigns, and event promotion strategy\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n - Plan and execute events within budget\n\n - Manage internal field and events communication between sales and marketing\n\n - Support strategic industry events through logistics planning\n\n - Represent Snowflake to counterparts at partners, vendors, and outside vendors\n\nRequirements:\n\n - 2+ years of experience in events, trade shows and/or field marketing\n\n - Experience in Salesforce, Marketo, Excel, Wordpress is an advantage\n\n - High proficiency with office productivity applications (e.g. Microsoft Office, Google Apps)\n\n - Bachelor’s Degree in Marketing, Communications, or similar field\n\n - Strong project management, time management, and execution skills\n\n - Embodies strong organizational skills\n\n - Ability to maintain an optimistic, approachable, and hands-on mentality\n\n - Demonstrates creative spark as expressed in ideas for messaging, creative design\n\n - Strong written and verbal skills in both English and Hebrew\n\n - Spanish and Italian would be an advantage\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
